                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Marriage deed (ketubba) dated Thursday 13 Nisan [1]606 Sel.
                            (= 31 March 1295 CE) in Fusṭāṭ. The ketubba is written under the
                            authority of David Maimonides (David b. Abraham b. Moses) as Nagid
                            (Raʾīs al-Yahūd). The groom is Nadiv b. Elʿazar b. Abraham, and the
                            bride is Sarah bat Elʿazar b. Abraham. There is a solitary signature
                            at the end of the deed: Saʿadya b. Judah, who was presumably the
                            scribe. Front and back of this manuscript were shot in the wrong order,
                            so the ketubba is in image 2. On the numbering of Add.3124A and
                            Add.3124B see Reif (1997: no. 933).</summary>
                        <msItem n="1">
                            <title>Legal document: ketubba</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="arc" otherLangs="heb">Aramaic; Hebrew</textLang>
                            <editor role="scr">Saʿadya b. Judah</editor>
                            <editor role="oth">David b. Abraham b. Moses Maimonides</editor>
                            <editor role="oth">Nadiv b. Elʿazar b. Abraham</editor>
                            <editor role="oth">Sarah bat Elʿazar b. Abraham</editor>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
